{"key":"post-9594033","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9594033</id>\n<content>Since the spores sit on the surface of the agar, I usually make my dishes up with less agar agar than called for so it will be a bit soupy.&amp;nbsp; Another alternative when germinating spores on agar is to place a drop of sterile water on top of the dish before you swipe the spores.&amp;nbsp; Until the spores re-hydrate, they can't germinate.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9594363</next>\n<prev>9594024</prev>\n<first>9593476</first>\n<last>9606520</last>\n<when>1231780353</when>\n<utime>01/12/09 07:12 PM</utime>\n</post>"}